It’s going down…

Haven’t park skated much in the past 3 months. Missing the nights when it was sunny ☀️ and warm out.

Somewhat miserable with 3 nagging injuries for the last 6 months. 🥲 Makes doing all your favorite tricks and learning new ones a lot less fun. Pulled hamstring, elbow tendinitis and a hip issue.

Been doing other hobbies (riding my motorcycle 🏍️ & playing roller derby 🛼) with reinvigorated goals to eat clean 🥗 and modify workouts 💪🏻 around the injuries while healing them. Starting to do yoga 🧘‍♀️ and get back into mediation.

How did you learn ☠️ Death Drops?

I did progressions, I failed, I made it. Simple. 🤡🤪

Who wants me to teach a class? Comment below. 👇🏼

#DeathDrop #Handstand #Gymnast #RollerSkates

(Pt 2) ⚠️ Dumb ways to die FULL VIDEO. ☠️

For those who asked to see the full video of my major backflip fail.

It was a timing error on my part. I waited too long to throw the flip. I lost the rotation momentum the ramp was gonna give me, so I ended up stalling mid air. ☠️

Lucky for me I was a gymnast for 16 years and had immediate body awareness of what went wrong and was able to think quickly. I looked for the ground and intentionally twisted my upper body just enough to land on my right shoulder and side of my face. 

I avoid landing on my head but my neck muscles did get tweaked and I was a little sore the next day.

#DumbWaysToDie #Fail #Fall #Bail #Oops #Flop

Trials and tribulations of learning a new trick at the skatepark. This one’s an illusion alley-oop half cab slide. Say that 3 times fast. 😂

An illusion is when you’re skating fakie looking over one shoulder but you spin in the other direction than the one you were facing as you approached the trick/spin.

Yay roller derby! Hometown Throwdown Day 1 you were amazing. Whipped out the old red sparkle racing stripes for the occasion.

@sydney.mayer.28 secured celebration champaign for day 3. My housemates were “day best”and our Airbnb kicked some tropical @$$. 

How amazing is @rachelblackman42 at rocking the Poo Bear 💛 backpack?!? 

Thanks to @victorianrollerderbyleague for giving me the cool vibes & nice person award after our game. 💙⚡️🐨

Day 2 was quite the problem…more on that later.

So…I won’t be skating for a little while. Warm-ups on day 2 of Hometown Throwdown didn’t go as planned. 🤕

Slippy slipped on the sport court surface to what felt like my right knee dislocating. While it was happening I saw my shin and foot twisting in the opposite direction of my thigh. 🤢 An observer said my legs “looked like a McDonald’s sign”. 😂 

Orthopedic appointment next week to find out what I might have injured.

Huge shoutout to my teammates @angelcityderby who babied me, waited on me hand and foot the rest of the weekend and got me safely to the airport. @cocob1804 @rachelblackman42 @stiletto389 @sydney.mayer.28 @boo.is.215lbs 

My lovely friends @katryna143 @hkauai also had a derby game the same weekend. After they heard I got injured, they wore my derby face paint at their game to cheer me up! ❤️

Goals to get back to skating strength. Fighting bears and doing death drops again.

Actually, playing roller derby is like fighting bears now that I come to think of it. 😂 

Just about 2 weeks post-injury. I can walk short distances now with the brace. Still can’t bend it past 90 degrees. Feels stable enough to start figuring out one-legged workouts. 💪🏻🤪

Still waiting to see the ortho to get some answers.

We take skating VERY SERIOUSLY. You should, too.

Always love the laughs and positive vibes of  @keanupagano @asiaskates @magguillotine

I mostly live in athletic clothes but I do clean up all right. 💁🏻‍♀️
